MANAMA, Bahrain, April 22, 2019/APO Group/ -- 
                                                        
                            The Minister of Foreign Affairs, Shaikh Khalid bin Ahmed bin Mohammed Al Khalifa conveyed a verbal message from His Majesty King Hamad bin Isa Al Khalifa of the Kingdom of Bahrain, to the Republic of Sudan’s head of transitional military council, Lieutenant General Abdel Fattah Al Burhan Abdelrahman, that included His Majesty’s greetings and keenness on supporting the Republic of Sudan during this crucial stage. 



The Minister also conveyed to Lieutenant General Abdel Fattah Al Burhan Abdelrahman the greetings of His Royal Highness the Prime Minister, Prince Khalifa bin Salman Al Khalifa, and His Royal Highness the Crown Prince, Deputy Supreme Commander and First Deputy Prime Minister, Prince Salman bin Hamad Al Khalifa, and their good wishes to him.
                                This came as the Minister of Foreign Affairs, Shaikh Khalid bin Ahmed bin Mohammed Al Khalifa was received by the Lieutenant General Abdel Fattah Al Burhan Abdelrahman
                            

This came as the Minister of Foreign Affairs, Shaikh Khalid bin Ahmed bin Mohammed Al Khalifa was received by the Lieutenant General Abdel Fattah Al Burhan Abdelrahman. Lieutenant General Abdel Fattah Al Burhan Abdelrahman expressed his sincere appreciation for His Majesty the King’s brotherly stance in supporting the Republic of Sudan in all circumstances, affirming that His Majesty the King’s position is unequivocal, given His Majesty’s keenness on ensuring the optimal welfare of Arab countries and their peoples. 

The Minister of Foreign Affairs expressed the Kingdom of Bahrain’s pride in its deep-rooted brotherly relations with the Republic of Sudan and its keenness to enhance these relations in all fields for the common interest of the two countries and brotherly peoples. He also affirmed the Kingdom of Bahrain’s solidarity with the Republic of Sudan and its support for everything that preserves its sovereignty, security and national unity, wishing the Republic of Sudan to overcome this crucial stage of its history and move towards further development and prosperity. 

The Minister of Foreign Affairs also commended the significant role played by the Republic of Sudan in the Saudi-led Arab Coalition to Restore Legitimacy in Yemen to establish peace and security in the Republic of Yemen, noting the valor of the Sudanese army and its performance of all the tasks assigned to it with efficiency and courage.

The Minister of Foreign Affairs, Shaikh Khalid bin Ahmed bin Mohammed Al Khalifa, issued a statement on his visit to the Republic of Sudan and his meeting with Lieutenant General Abdel Fattah Al Burhan Abdelrahman.